---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="Building the World Model — Epic Chats"
      description="Henry and Ada design a shared cognitive architecture for the Enterprise Crew: world.json, three pi-research tracks, autonomy simulations, and the first multi-agent orchestration loop."
    />
    <style>
      body { background: #0D0B09; color: #E8DCC8; }

      main {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 3rem 1.5rem 5rem;
      }

      .back-link {
        display: inline-block;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: #8B7E6A;
        text-decoration: none;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        transition: color 0.15s;
      }
      .back-link:hover { color: #C87533; }

      .page-meta {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 10px;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }

      .participant-chip {
        background: #1A1510;
        border: 1px solid #2A241E;
        color: #8B7E6A;
        font-size: 11px;
        font-weight: 600;
        padding: 2px 8px;
        border-radius: 2px;
        font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
        letter-spacing: 0.03em;
      }

      .page-date {
        color: #5C5248;
        font-size: 12px;
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      }

      h1 {
        font-family: Georgia, serif;
        font-size: 2.25rem;
        font-weight: 400;
        color: #E8DCC8;
        margin: 0 0 0.875rem;
        line-height: 1.2;
      }

      .subtitle {
        color: #8B7E6A;
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.65;
        margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
        max-width: 600px;
      }

      .context-box {
        background: #110F0C;
        border: 1px solid #2A241E;
        border-left: 3px solid #C87533;
        border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
        padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
      }

      .context-box .eyebrow {
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: #C87533;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      }

      .context-box p {
        color: #8B7E6A;
        font-size: 0.925rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
      }

      .context-box p:last-of-type { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }

      .context-box :global(code) {
        background: #1A1510;
        border: 1px solid #2A241E;
        padding: 1px 6px;
        border-radius: 3px;
        font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
        font-size: 87%;
        color: #C87533;
      }

      .stats {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-top: 1rem;
      }

      .stat {
        background: #1A1510;
        border: 1px solid #2A241E;
        padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 2px;
      }

      .stat-label {
        color: #5C5248;
        font-size: 10px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      }

      .stat-value {
        color: #C87533;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
      }

      .findings {
        margin-top: 3rem;
        border-top: 1px solid #2A241E;
        padding-top: 2.5rem;
      }

      .findings h2 {
        font-family: Georgia, serif;
        font-size: 1.35rem;
        font-weight: 400;
        color: #E8DCC8;
        margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
      }

      .finding-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(210px, 1fr));
        gap: 1px;
        background: #2A241E;
        border: 1px solid #2A241E;
      }

      .finding {
        background: #0D0B09;
        padding: 1.25rem;
      }

      .finding h3 {
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: #C87533;
        margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      }

      .finding p {
        color: #8B7E6A;
        font-size: 0.875rem;
        line-height: 1.65;
        margin: 0;
      }

      .chat-embed {
        margin: 2rem 0;
        border-radius: 8px;
        overflow: hidden;
        border: 1px solid #2A241E;
      }

      .chat-iframe {
        width: 100%;
        height: 700px;
        border: none;
        display: block;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <a href="/epic-chats" class="back-link">← Epic Chats</a>

      <div class="page-meta">
        <span class="participant-chip">Henry</span>
        <span class="participant-chip">Ada</span>
        <span class="page-date">March 24, 2026</span>
      </div>

      <h1>Building the World Model</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        From autonomy architecture simulations to world.json — the session where the Enterprise Crew got a shared brain.
        Three pi-research runs. One canonical world model. The beginning of coherent multi-agent reasoning.
      </p>

      <div class="context-box">
        <div class="eyebrow">What happened here</div>
        <p>
          After running autonomy architecture simulations (6 architectures, scored across context sharing,
          failure resilience, and cascade risk), Henry and Ada realized they were solving the wrong problem.
          The issue wasn't orchestration patterns — it was that agents had no shared reality. Each agent
          reasoned from isolated files. There was no single source of truth.
        </p>
        <p>
          This session built that foundation: <code>world.json</code>, a propagation model, three parallel
          pi-research tracks to stress-test the design, and the first concrete answer to
          "how does a signal from Henry reach the right agents at the right time?"
        </p>
        <div class="stats">
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat-label">Architecture E+D composite</span>
            <span class="stat-value">8.85</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat-label">p99 propagation latency</span>
            <span class="stat-value">0.299h</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat-label">Scale tested</span>
            <span class="stat-value">50 agents</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="chat-embed">
        <iframe
          src="/epic-chats/world-model-embed.html"
          class="chat-iframe"
          title="Building the World Model — conversation transcript"
          loading="lazy"
          scrolling="yes"
        ></iframe>
      </div>

      <div class="findings">
        <h2>What we found</h2>
        <div class="finding-grid">
          <div class="finding">
            <h3>Track 1 — Propagation</h3>
            <p>Selective propagation (notify only subscribed agents) outperforms broadcast at scale. Dampening rules matter more than routing. An offline agent should buffer signals, not drop them.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="finding">
            <h3>Track 2 — Structure</h3>
            <p>Optimistic concurrency with field ownership is the right consistency model for concurrent agent writes. Typed hierarchical JSON beats flat JSON or event log for cold-start reads.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="finding">
            <h3>Track 3 — Synthesis</h3>
            <p>Architecture E (Intent Graph) inside a D (Orchestrator Loop) wrapper achieves &gt;8.5 composite with controlled cascade risk. The world model must encode agent subscriptions, not just entity state.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
